  "text": "The xDS v3 transport protocol implementation in Envoy (v1.31.2) is organized across two architectural layers: a legacy implementation and a unified template-based implementation.\n\n## Core Architecture\n\n**GrpcSubscriptionImpl Adapter** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h/.cc):\nThis adapter bridges typed Subscription objects with the untyped GrpcMux. It handles per-xDS API statistics and logging, serving as the primary interface between Envoy's subscription callbacks and the underlying gRPC multiplexer.\n\n**GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.h/.cc):\nThis factory is responsible for selecting between State-of-the-World (SotW) and Delta xDS modes. The factory creates appropriate GrpcMux instances based on runtime feature flags:\n- Uses `Config::XdsMux::GrpcMuxSotw` when `envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux` is enabled (new unified template)\n- Falls back to `Config::GrpcMuxImpl` for legacy SotW implementation\n- For Delta mode, uses `Config::XdsMux::GrpcMuxDelta` with unified mux or `Config::NewGrpcMuxImpl` for legacy\n\n## Legacy Implementations\n\n**SotW GrpcMuxImpl** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc):\nLegacy State-of-the-World implementation using gRPC ADS (Aggregated Discovery Service) protocol. Manages subscriptions to one or more resource types, handling watch registration, discovery request queuing, and gRPC stream management using DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse.\n\n**Delta NewGrpcMuxImpl** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc):\nLegacy Delta xDS implementation for incremental resource updates. Uses DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse for bandwidth-efficient resource synchronization with server-side change tracking.\n\n## Unified Template-Based Implementation\n\n**XdsMux::GrpcMuxImpl Template** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc):\nA generic template class parameterized by:\n- S: SubscriptionState type (either SotwSubscriptionState or DeltaSubscriptionState)\n- F: SubscriptionStateFactory type (SotwSubscriptionStateFactory or DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory)\n- RQ: Request type (DiscoveryRequest or DeltaDiscoveryRequest)\n- RS: Response type (DiscoveryResponse or DeltaDiscoveryResponse)\n\nThis unifies the SotW and Delta implementations under a single template, reducing code duplication. Two specializations are provided:\n\n**GrpcMuxSotw** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h):\nSpecialization using SotwSubscriptionState and DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse. Implements State-of-the-World semantics where the server sends complete resource lists.\n\n**GrpcMuxDelta** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h):\nSpecialization using DeltaSubscriptionState and DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse. Implements Delta xDS semantics with incremental updates.\n\n## Subscription State Management\n\n**BaseSubscriptionState** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/subscription_state.h):\nAbstract base class template tracking protocol state for individual xDS-over-gRPC sessions per type_url. Manages TTL expiration, update tracking, and delegates to WatchMap for resource callbacks.\n\n**SotwSubscriptionState** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h/.cc):\nState-of-the-World implementation tracking current resource versions, ACK nonces, and handling full resource list responses.\n\n**DeltaSubscriptionState** (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h/.cc):\nDelta xDS implementation tracking resource subscription interest, server version tracking, and managing incremental add/remove operations.\n\n## Protocol Flow\n\nConfiguration subscriptions flow through: ConfigSubscriptionFactory -> GrpcSubscriptionImpl -> GrpcMux (legacy or unified) -> GrpcStream -> gRPC channel. The factory's runtime feature flag selection determines whether the unified template-based implementation or legacy implementations are used, enabling smooth migration from separate implementations to the unified template design."
}

